President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Victor M. Mendez, currently the Administrator of the Federal Highway Administration, was nominated for the position of Deputy Secretary of the Department of Transportation. Robert S. Adler, currently a Commissioner on the Consumer Product Safety Commission, was nominated for the position of Commissioner. Peter Rogoff, currently the Federal Transit Administrator, was nominated for the position of Under Secretary for Policy at the Department of Transportation. Ted Osius, an Associate Professor at the National War College, was nominated for the position of Ambassador to the Socialist Republic of Vietnam. Joan A. Polaschik, currently the Director of the Office of Egypt and Levant Affairs at the Department of State, was nominated for the position of Ambassador to the People's Democratic Republic of Algeria. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Rev. Thomas J. Reese, S.J., a Senior Analyst for the National Catholic Reporter, and Eric P. Schwartz, the Dean of the Humphrey School of Public Affairs at the University of Minnesota, to key Administration posts.